.TH "comedi_alloc_subdevices" 9 "comedi_alloc_subdevices" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
comedi_alloc_subdevices \- Allocate subdevices for COMEDI device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" comedi_alloc_subdevices
.BI "(struct comedi_device *dev "  ","
.BI "int num_subdevices "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
COMEDI device.
.IP "num_subdevices" 12
Number of subdevices to allocate.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates and initializes an array of \fIstruct comedi_subdevice\fP for the
COMEDI device.  If successful, sets \fIdev->subdevices\fP to point to the
first one and \fIdev->n_subdevices\fP to the number.

Returns 0 on success, -EINVAL if \fInum_subdevices\fP is < 1, or -ENOMEM if
failed to allocate the memory.
